Thanks for writing to Ask Dr. Math, Xaley!

Substitute x^2 = y.  Then you want the remainder when 3*y^2 - 5*y + 4
is divided by y + 2.  Use the Remainder Theorem.  Is that easier?

Feel free to reply if I can help further with this question.


